<p>I want to analysis web page when loaded successfully. </p>  <p>I know that WebKitWebView class provides the “load-changed” signal.</p>  <p><a href="http://webkitgtk.org/reference/webkit2gtk/unstable/WebKitWebView.html#WebKitWebView-load-changed" rel="nofollow">http://webkitgtk.org/reference/webkit2gtk/unstable/WebKitWebView.html#WebKitWebView-load-changed</a></p>  <p>But when meet the following javascript codes,</p>  <pre><code>location.href = 'hello.html'; </code></pre>  <p>WEBKIT_LOAD_FINISHED event is emitted twice the first page and hello.html page.</p>  <p>I have to analysis page when reach the last page. How to know this page is the last page?</p>  <p>WEBKIT_LOAD_REDIRECTED event only emitted page redirected by http response not javascript.</p>  <p>I was tried to know it using WebKitBackForwardList and javascript hook.</p>  <p>The WebKitBackForwardList history does not exist and can't hook window.location setter.</p>  <p>Because It can't be reconfigurable object property.</p>